<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1322,1649,1875]" lastBlockId="10.[264,1323,284,430]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Diagnosis: Females can be distinguished from all species by having a longitudinal dark band on the ventral abdomen in conjunction with three clear stripes on each side of the dorsal abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[509,597,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 44" captionStartId="13.[264,383,1220,1244]" captionTargetBox="[278,1316,473,1200]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[260,1349,449,1215]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 44. Cephalothorax and abdominal color pattern of Cyriocosmus species. (40) C. versicolor male (MACN­Ar 6525), Argentina, Salta. (41) C. bertae male holotype (IBSP 4950), Brazil, Acre, Rio Branco. (42) C. leetzi male (ICN­Ar 33), Casanare, Vereda El Guineo, Agua Azul. (43) C. elegans male (RCW) Tobago Island, Speyside. (44) C. fasciatus male lectotype, Brazil, Cuminá River. From top to bottom: cephalothorax, dorsal abdomen, ventral abdomen and lateral abdomen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170720/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[563,597,284,310]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
). The male can be distinguished from all other species, except 
<emphasis box="[264,364,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName box="[264,359,324,349]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Cyriocosmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ritae">C. ritae</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
by having a longitudinal dark band on the ventral abdomen. It differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Cyriocosmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ritae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C. ritae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a short paraembolic apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[821,927,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="5.[264,383,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[308,1282,327,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[277,1319,310,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Left palpal bulbs of Cyriocosmus. (1 – 2) C. versicolor (MACN­Ar 6525), Argentina, Salta. (3 – 4) C. bertae holotype (IBSP 4950), Brazil, Acre, Rio Branco. (5 – 6) C. leetzi (ICN­Ar 33), Casanare, Vereda El Guineo, Agua Azul. (7 – 8) C. elegans (RCW), Tobago Island, Speyside. (9 – 10) C. fasciatus lectotype (MNRJ), Brazil, Cuminá River. (1, 3, 5, 7, 9) retrolateral, (2, 4, 6, 8, 10) prolateral. Scale bar = 1 mm. E = embolus, PA = paraembolic apophysis, PS = prolateral superior keel." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170715/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
